es not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":32,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John William Tregarthen was born in 1350, in Branscombe, Devon, England, his father, John Tregarthin Jr, was 23 and his mother, Jane Trethurffe, was 21. He married Maria Jenkin on 4 June 1375, in Madron, Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1444, at the age of 94."},"et":{"1350–1444":"1350–1444","1360–Female":"1360–Surnud","1390–1445":"1390–1445","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1327":"1327","1445":"1445","1444":"1444","4 June 1375":"4. juuni 1375","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","Madron, Cornwall, England":"Madron, Cornwall, England","Treleigh, Cornwall, England":"Treleigh, Cornwall, England","Branscombe, Devon, England":"Branscombe, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1350–1444":"1350–1444","1360–Female":"1360–Kuollut","1390–1445":"1390–1445","1327–Male":"1327–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1327":"1327","1445":"1445","1444":"1444","4 June 1375":"4. kesäkuuta 1375","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","Madron, Cornwall, England":"Madron, Cornwall, England","Treleigh, Cornwall, England":"Treleigh, Corn